# Copy punctuation

## No em dashes or en dashes

Never use em dashes (`—`, U+2014) or en dashes (`–`, U+2013) in user-facing copy, titles, meta descriptions, alt text, or comments meant for the page.

Use a **hyphen** (`-`, ASCII hyphen-minus) instead:

| Avoid | Use |
|-------|-----|
| `Andrew Sheerin — About` | `Andrew Sheerin - About` |
| `execution — helping teams` | `execution - helping teams` |
| `2004–2015` | `2004-2015` |
| `Nudgestock — The Persuasive Power of Play` | `Nudgestock - The Persuasive Power of Play` |

## When editing existing files

If you touch a file that contains `—` or `–` in copy, replace with `-` in the same edit unless Andrew explicitly asks to keep them.

## Exceptions

- Arrow glyphs in product UI screenshots (do not rewrite image assets)
- Code, URLs, or third-party quotes that must stay verbatim — flag to Andrew instead of silently changing
